  "title": {
    "en": "Jesus Begins to Teach"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en": [
      "After being tested in the wilderness, Jesus returns to Galilee.",
      "He begins teaching in the synagogues."
    ]
  },
  "blocks": {
    "en": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "return",
        "icon": "school",
        "label": { "en": "Teaching in Galilee" },
        "lines": [
          "Jesus returned to Galilee in the power of the Spirit,",
          "and news about him spread through the whole countryside.",
          "He taught in their synagogues,",
          "and everyone praised him.",
          "All spoke well of him",
          "and were amazed at the gracious words",
          "that came from his lips."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "persecution",
        "icon": "campaign",
        "label": { "en": "Blessed in Persecution" },
        "lines": [
          "“Blessed are you",
          "when people insult you,",
          "persecute you",
          "and falsely say all kinds of evil against you because of me.",
          "Rejoice and be glad,",
          "because great is your reward in heaven,",
          "for in the same way",
          "they persecuted the prophets",
          "who were before you.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "law",
        "icon": "menu_book",
        "label": { "en": "The Law and the Prophets" },
        "lines": [
          "“Do not think that I have come",
          "to abolish the Law or the Prophets;",
          "I have not come to abolish them",
          "but to fulfill them.”"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "question": {
    "en": "What do you notice about how Jesus speaks about the prophets—and about his relationship to the Law?"
  },
  "further_reading": {
    "en": ["Luke 4:14–15", "Matthew 5:10–17"]
  }
}
